# get average cases of each country

avgcases = []

for i in df['country'].unique():
    coun = df.loc[df['country']==i]
    coun['dailyconfirmed'] = coun.confirmed.diff()
    avg = coun['dailyconfirmed'].sum() / len(coun)
    print(i, avg)
    avgcases.append([i, avg])

Conclusion¶

  1. Real-world data is not ready for analysis.
  2. Read-world data needs to be cleaned and transformed.
  3. Pandas (Python) is a valuable tool for data cleaning and transformation.
